reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great addition to my bedroom
reviews.reviewText: This product was very easy to put together. Took me less than five minutes. It is very sturdy and fits comfortably on my sink counter. It fits perfectly in the corner. This product is worth every dollar and it looks good in my bathroom.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars It’s bigger than I thought
reviews.reviewText: It’s simple yet beautiful and spacious. Easy to assemble and sturdy. Love this product!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Coner Shelf
reviews.reviewText: Weenson Kitchen Countertop Organizer Corner Shelf is great for my space. I DYI remodeled my backsplash and area around my stove. I needed for space for my spices. I had limited space on that side of my stove. I found this corner shelf and it look like it would work and it was perfect! The shelf was easy to put together. very sturdy. In my photo you also see 3 more Amazon items: the Audmore Kitchen utensil rack, Yipcazo Peel and stick tiles and Calpalmy Metal backsplash. The top shelf can be "flipped" for right or left. The shelf has a good bit of room under it for larger things. The 2 shelves gives you lots of room for spice bottles. I am very happy with this shelf.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 24, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I have this used as 2 separate shelves for my double sinks in the bathroom. They work well. They could be sturdier for sure but I haven't had any issues specifically with the quality. I find that my things are much more organized and the area is easier to clean over all since getting these.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great space saver & looks nice!
reviews.reviewText: Absolutely love it! I got the brown one and it has the option to be stacked or use the two shelves individually. I stacked mine and it literally saves me SO much counter space. My husband can finally use the second sink in our master bath now because there’s room for his things. Definitely going to buy a second one for my side of the counter to make even more counter space. 10/10 recommend
